Friese (1901): Mentioned from 
<collectingCountry box="[644,703,691,717]" name="Syria" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Syria</collectingCountry>
without locality details.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1437,618,825]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">
There has been a great deal of confusion on the old records of this taxon in Northern Africa and the Levant. These records could be either referebale to either 
<taxonomicName authority="Maa, 1970" authorityName="Maa" authorityYear="1970" box="[643,917,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcatipes">
<emphasis box="[643,788,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">X. sulcatipes</emphasis>
Maa, 1970
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith, 1854" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[958,1228,762,789]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ustulata">
<emphasis box="[958,1080,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">X. ustulata</emphasis>
Smith, 1854
</taxonomicName>
(Terzo &amp; Ramont 2014), but we feel confident that they do not correspond to true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[867,1019,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hottentotta">
<emphasis box="[867,1019,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">X. hottentotta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
